  "prompt": "So, can a sentence begin with the word \"so\"?",
  "response": "Yes, a sentence can begin with the word \"so.\" Using \"so\" at the beginning of a sentence is often used in informal writing or speaking to introduce a result, conclusion, or continuation of a previous thought. For example:\n\n\"So, I decided to go to the party after all.\"\n\nHowever, in formal writing, it is generally recommended to use more precise or varied conjunctions to start sentences.",
